            <bug_when>2013-03-01 16:46:11 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>You may use an @type doc comment for the data item, to specify the intended type if the static member is initialized with &#39;null&#39; or &#39;undefined&#39;:

  /**
   * @type {Map}
   */
   foo : null,

This is often the case when the actual initialisation happens in the constructor of the class. In these cases, the @type info should override the type inferred from the init value. In all other cases, i.e. when the init value is a proper value, the inferred type should take precedence over any @type annotation in the Apiviewer.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
